• *Natural language ontology*. With collaborators I have proposed treating
  [degrees as Carlsonian kinds of states][degreekinds], and in [older
  work][takso] introducing manners as a type in the model by treating
  them as [event kinds][takso]. I've also worked on [the ontology of
  scales][compositeMPsSUB], on [null individuals][zeroSALT], and on [the
  distinction][nominalizationsSuB] between degree concepts and abstract mass
  qualities.
  
• *Nominal gradability, degree modification, and gradability across
  categories*. I've examined how [size adjectives contribute to
  nominal gradability][bigidiot] (_big idiot_), and how [other degree
  expressions][faces] do too. More recently I've worked on [degree
  nominalizations][nominalizationsSuB]. An older paper considers [extreme
  degree modifiers][extremefinal] like _flat-out_ and [another][leipzig],
  ad-adjectival adverbs like _remarkably_. I've also worked on [metalinguistic
  comparatives][metaling], which have a crosscategorial distribution. [This
  ancient paper][almostSALT] draws attention to crosscategorial uses of
  particles like _almost_.

