• *Manner modification*. More or less recently I've worked on why manner
  descriptions tend to be [unexpectedly definite][hotzesquib] and how manner
  and other modifier questions are formed in [Ktunaxa][ktquestionssub].
  With collaborators, I've proposed that 'manners' can be understood
  as kinds of events. This has also come up in [this paper focused on
  degrees][degreekinds], but the idea dates originally from [this][takso]
  nearly quarter-century old proceedings paper. I've also worked on why [_how_
  often gets non-manner readings][propositionalhow].

• *Adjectival lexical semantics and nonlocal readings of adjectives*.
  This paper attempts [a general theory of nonlocal readings][nonlocal],
  and you can also look at [this earlier attempt][nonlocalSUB] or an early
  assessment of the data in my [book][book]. They also come up with respect to
  _[single][single]_ and [bare singulars][piano] in English. Years ago I worked
  on [extreme adjectives][extremefinal] (also, in an earlier incarnation,
  [here][extreme]). I've also worked on adjectives like _[whole][wholesshort]_.

